                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Anyone here have a copy of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/1593150202/qid=1099906307/sr=8-6/ref=pd_csp_6/002-7967929-0029605?v=glance&s=books&n=507846" target="_blank" class="postlink">Everquest: Rogues hour</a>?
<br />

<br />
So how is it? 
<br />
Worth getting it in hardcover now or wait for the paperback edition? what era does it cover? EQlive era (PC) or set in the "past" or "future" (EQOA or EQ2) of Norrath?
<br />

<br />
How are your reviews?
<br />
Does it reflect the feel and atmosphere of Norrath well or is it just a generic fantasy novel with EQ names tacked on?
<br />

<br />
