                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For a stable population, the death rate of female dark elves has to match the rate of female dark elf replacement.
<br />

<br />
The rate of male births has to pass 1/day to get your 'nightly male dark elf death' quote above.
<br />

<br />
X% of the society is female.  Y% of the children are female
<br />
Pop = population
<br />

<br />
Pop * X% * (1-Y%) * BirthRate - NormalDeathRate * Pop * (1-X%) = Extra male deaths
<br />

<br />
In other words:
<br />
Number of Males born per year - Normal male deaths = Extra male deaths
<br />

<br />
A stable female population means:
<br />
Y% * BirthRate = NormalDeathRate
<br />
In other words:
<br />
female birth rate = female death rate
<br />

<br />

<br />
Pop * BirthRate *  [  (1-Y%)X% -Y%(1-X%) ] = Extra male deaths
<br />
The part in the square []s is:
<br />
[X%-Y%X% - Y% +Y%X%]
<br />
or
<br />
[ X%-Y% ]
<br />
"X%-Y%" is "the percent of females in the population there are above the expected percentage, given the male/female birth rates"
<br />

<br />
Let Z% = X%-Y%
<br />

<br />
so we get:
<br />
Pop * BirthRate *  [ Z% ] = Extra male deaths
<br />

<br />

<br />
With a birth per elven female every 50 years:
<br />

<br />
20000 * 1/50 * [ Z% ] = Extra male deaths
<br />
or
<br />
Z% = Extra male deaths / 400
<br />

<br />
To have 365 extra male deaths every year, Z%=X%-Y% must be 91.25%(!), which means Y% &lt; 8.75%.
<br />

<br />
By female population replacement:
<br />
Y% = NormalDeathRate / BirthRate
<br />
or
<br />
Y% = NormalDeathRate * 50
<br />

<br />
NormalDeathRate * 50 &lt; 8.75%
<br />
or
<br />
NormalDeathRate &lt; 0.175%
<br />
in order for the population to be stable, and for 1 extra male dark elf to die every day, beyond what is expected of females.
<br />

<br />
Lets set NormalDeathRate to 0.15% (on the high end), which sets Y% to 7.5%  Then we get:
<br />

<br />
20000 * X% * 92.5% /50 - 0.15% * 20000 * (1-X%) = 365
<br />
370 * X% - 30 * (1-X%) = 365
<br />
370 * X% - 30 * 1 + 30 *X%) = 365
<br />
400 X% = 395
<br />
X% = 98.75%
<br />
The socieity is 98.75% female, and 92.5% of live births are male.
<br />

<br />
The death rate of females, per year, is 0.15%
<br />
The death rate of males, per year, is 59.4%
<br />

<br />
Average age of death of females is 666.7.
<br />
Average age of death of males is under 2 years.
<br />

<br />
There are 19750 females and 250 males in society.
<br />
365.375 males die per year
<br />
29.625 females die per year
<br />
There are about 395 births per year, of which about 29.625 are female and 365.375 are male.
<br />

<br />
I don't think a death-a-day of male dark elves makes sense.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
