                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know that I personally have enjoyed how Elaine Cunningham and the War of the Spider Queen series brought the Underdark to "life" in how they describe the dark elves and the cities around them better then Salvatore did. I know Salvatores Cantcile? series was interesting, though it was kinda funny how he made out Denier, minor god of runes, into a MAJOR FORCE of good and knowledge in the Realms <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />. 
<br />

<br />
 I know my most hated author for Forgotten Realms books will always be... Ed Greenwood. As my little brother likes to point out, he makes is excessive fond of everyone running around naked, is fond of making the his characters the most powerful in the world in a rather inconsistant manner, and makes it sound like Elminster is the only reason the universe still exists today. The way he has Elminster or the Simbul run around killing people, makes you wonder why Zhentil Keep is soooo dangerous since Manshoon isnt even a archmage! His "war of shadows" books that was supppose to take time during the Fall of the Gods... doesnt even follow the timeline at all. Here Elminster was supposedly given all of Mystra's power as she was cast out of the heavens in a instant and all it did was make him tear in the eyes alittle... The last person that happened to in the realms was Karsus, and that process made him into a god though I guess you could say the shock also killed him even if he does still live on as a demigod, destroyed the "weave" of magic around the realms, and the only reason the world "lived" through the destruction was Mystra commiting suicide.
<br />

<br />
 Ah well, as anyone you bothers to read this can tell, Vahen is a bitter person who reads to much into fantasy books.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Vahen, Dark Elf Enchanter
